Liverpool has officially reached their third champions league final in five years after qualifying in a stunning comeback win over Villarreal in Spain Liverpool fans are screaming from the rooftops today and booking their trips to Paris, after qualifying for the Champions League final. The club performed a turnaround like no other in the second half, to take the win 3-2, winning 5-2 on aggregate. It wasn't all smooth sailing for the English Club though, with Villarreal dominating the first half up two-nil.